# Copy into the Vercel dashboard's Environment Variables (Project Settings
# -> Environment Variables) for the app, and into GitHub repo secrets
# (Settings -> Secrets and variables -> Actions) for the scraper/
# classification workflows in .github/workflows/. Never commit a filled-in
# copy of this file.
#
# (This also still works for a Railway deploy per the pre-existing
# railway.json/frontend/railway.json — just set DATABASE_URL there too. See
# BUILD_NOTES.md.)

# --- Database (Neon Postgres) ---
# Use Neon's POOLED connection string (the one with "-pooler" in the
# hostname), not the direct/unpooled one. Vercel functions and GitHub
# Actions runs are short-lived and can spin up many concurrent connections;
# going through Neon's pooler keeps that from exhausting Postgres' own
# connection limit. Get it from the Neon dashboard -> Connection Details ->
# "Pooled connection". Example:
#   postgresql://user:password@ep-xxxx-pooler.region.aws.neon.tech/dbname?sslmode=require
DATABASE_URL=

# --- Admin auth (backend/src/lib/auth.ts) ---
# Shared-password admin login for /admin.html. If unset, a random
# username/password/session-secret is generated at process startup instead
# — fine for local dev, but USELESS in production/serverless: every cold
# start would silently rotate the password and invalidate all sessions. Set
# real values in Vercel. See BUILD_NOTES.md ("Admin auth is still a
# generated-per-process fallback") for the open question here.
ADMIN_USERNAME=admin
ADMIN_PASSWORD=
# Secret used to HMAC-sign admin session tokens. Generate with:
#   node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
JWT_SECRET=

# --- Embeddings / related organizations (backend/src/lib/embeddings.ts) ---
# Powers the cross-category "related organizations" feature (see
# BUILD_NOTES.md). Used to call OpenAI's embeddings endpoint
# (model: text-embedding-3-small) whenever an opportunity is scraped,
# reclassified, approved, or edited. If unset, embedding generation is
# skipped (logs one warning) and the feature stays fully wired but inert —
# opportunities.embedding stays null and every `relatedOrgs` response is an
# empty array. Once set, run `npm run backfill:embeddings` (from backend/)
# to populate embeddings for rows that were created before the key existed.
OPENAI_API_KEY=

# --- Server (local dev / Railway only — unused by the Vercel function) ---
# Vercel sets NODE_ENV=production automatically and does not use PORT at
# all (api/index.ts is a serverless function, not a listening process).
# Both only matter for `npm run dev:backend` or a Railway deploy.
PORT=3000
NODE_ENV=production
